	(5260,2077,'_mcb-products','[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Budweiser_-_KOB_70x_46_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2366\" alt=\"Budweiser_-_KOB_70x_46_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Budweiser_-_KOB_70x_46_165.png\" width=\"46\" height=\"165\" /></a>Budweiser</h3>\r\n<h4>The King of Beers</h4>\r\n<h4>ABV: 5%</h4>\r\nBudweiser is brewed with time-honored methods including “kraeusening” for natural carbonation and Beechwood aging, which results in unparalleled balance and character.\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Bud_Black_Crown_btl_clear_46_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2367\" alt=\"Bud_Black_Crown_btl_clear_46_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Bud_Black_Crown_btl_clear_46_165.png\" width=\"46\" height=\"165\" /></a>Budweiser Black Crown</h3>\r\n<h5>Golden Amber Lager</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 6%</h5>\r\nA new 6% ABV golden amber lager from Budweiser that is distinctively flavorful, yet smooth and drinkable.Black Crown is brewed with toasted caramel malt and finished over beechwood chips for a distinctively smooth, flavorful finish.  Brewed using Budweiser’s 1876 yeast strain and signature aging process.\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Budweiser_SELECT_100x360_clr_46_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2369\" alt=\"Budweiser_SELECT_100x360_clr_46_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Budweiser_SELECT_100x360_clr_46_165.png\" width=\"46\" height=\"165\" /></a>Budweiser SELECT</h3>\r\n<h4>99 Calories</h4>\r\n<h4>ABV: 4.3%</h4>\r\nBudweiser Select delivers it all - a bold taste, full-flavor and a clean finish, it\'s the best of both worlds. This full flavored, low calorie beer has a slightly dark, golden color with aromas of toasted grains and Bavarian hops. Subtle malty taste notes carry through to a crisp,clean hop finish.\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Bud_Select_55_CLEAR_46_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2370\" alt=\"Bud_Select_55_CLEAR_46_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Bud_Select_55_CLEAR_46_165.png\" width=\"46\" height=\"165\" /></a>Budweiser SELECT 55</h3>\r\n<h5>\"The world\'s lightest beer!\"</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 2.4%</h5>\r\nSelect 55 is brewed with specialty malts and a blend of imported and domestic hopping. This beer has a light golden color and offers aroma notes of toasted malt and subtle hopping.\r\n\r\nSelect 55 is the lightest beer in the world with fewer calories than any other beer option currently available. Per 12-ounce serving, Select 55 has 55 calories and 1.9 grams of carbs.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Bud_Ice_clear_46_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2368\" alt=\"Bud_Ice_clear_46_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Bud_Ice_clear_46_165.png\" width=\"46\" height=\"165\" /></a>Bud Ice</h3>\r\n<h4>Cold-Filtered</h4>\r\n<h4>ABV: 5.5%</h4>\r\nIntroduced nationally in 1995, Bud Ice is American\'s first draft beer to be ice brewed. Anheuser-Busch\'s exclusive ice-brewing process takes the beer to a temperature below freezing, leading to the formation of ice crystals. The beer then rests in storage at 28 degrees Fahrenheit for several days before being cold-filtered and packaged, resulting in a rich, smooth draft taste that is remarkably easy to drink. Bud Ice Light is a light alternative to this ice-brewed beverage.'),
