	(6612,2132,'_mcb-products','[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Goose_Island_312_btl_70x259_clr_45_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2435\" alt=\"Goose_Island_312_btl_70x259_clr_45_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Goose_Island_312_btl_70x259_clr_45_165.png\" width=\"45\" height=\"165\" /></a>Goose Island 312 Urban Wheat</h3>\r\n<h5>WHEAT BEER</h5>\r\n<h5>YEAR ROUND</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 4.2%</h5>\r\nInspired by the city of Chicago and densely populated with flavor, 312\'s spicy aroma of Cascade hops is followed by a crisp, fruity ale flavor delivered in a smooth, creamy body that’s immensely refreshing.\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Goose_Island_Honkers_Ale_btl_70x259_clr_45_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2436\" alt=\"Goose_Island_Honkers_Ale_btl_70x259_clr_45_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Goose_Island_Honkers_Ale_btl_70x259_clr_45_165.png\" width=\"45\" height=\"165\" /></a>Goose Island Honkers Ale</h3>\r\n<h5>ENGLISH STYLE BITTER</h5>\r\n<h5>YEAR ROUND</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 4.2%</h5>\r\nInspired by visits to English country pubs, Honker\'s Ale combines a fruity hop aroma with a rich malt middle to create a perfectly balanced beer. Immensely drinkable, Honker\'s Ale is not only the beer you can trust but one you\'ll look forward to time and again.\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Goose_Island_IPA_DRY_btl_70x259_clr_45_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2432\" alt=\"Goose_Island_IPA_DRY_btl_70x259_clr_45_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Goose_Island_IPA_DRY_btl_70x259_clr_45_165.png\" width=\"45\" height=\"165\" /></a>Goose Island India Pale Ale</h3>\r\n<h5>IPA</h5>\r\n<h5>YEAR ROUND</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 5.9%</h5>\r\nThis IPA recalls a time when ales shipped from England to India were highly hopped to preserve their distinct taste during the long journey. The result is a hop lover\'s dream with a fruity aroma, set off by a dry malt middle, and long hop finish.\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/GOOSE-SUMMER.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2472\" alt=\"GOOSE SUMMER\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/GOOSE-SUMMER.jpg\" width=\"48\" height=\"166\" /></a>Goose Island Summertime</h3>\r\n<h4>Seasonal (March-August)</h4>\r\n<h5>ABV: 5.1%</h5>\r\nThe color of sunshine, with a light fruity aroma and a hint of fruity acidity, Goose Island Summertime is the perfect summer session ale. A Kölsch beer brewed in the traditional German fashion, you’ll find yourself enjoying and savoring each sip of summertime as much as you do those hot summer days and cool summer nights.\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/GOOSE-NUT-ROLL.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2473\" alt=\"GOOSE NUT ROLL\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/GOOSE-NUT-ROLL.jpg\" width=\"47\" height=\"165\" /></a>Goose Island Nut Brown Ale</h3>\r\n<h5>YEAR ROUND</h5>\r\n<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: 11px; font-weight: bold;\">ABV: 5.3%</span>\r\n\r\nOur Nut Brown Ale combines the finest domestic and imported malts to produce a chestnut-hued ale of unusual complexity. Subtle notes of chocolate, honey and fine tobacco give this ale an enjoyable and satisfying “nutty” finish.\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Goose_Island_Harvest_Ale_btl_46_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2433\" alt=\"Goose_Island_Harvest_Ale_btl_46_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Goose_Island_Harvest_Ale_btl_46_165.png\" width=\"46\" height=\"165\" /></a>Goose Island Harvest Ale</h3>\r\n<h5>AMERICAN EXTRA SPECIAL BITTER</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 5.7%</h5>\r\nBrewed in honor of the Harvest season this copper colored ESB is made with Cascade hops and the richest Midwestern malts. A fruity American hop aroma and a toasty malt character make Goose Island Harvest Ale an extra special beer worthy of your devotion.\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Goose_Island_Sofie_12-oz_46_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2430\" alt=\"Goose_Island_Sofie_12-oz_46_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Goose_Island_Sofie_12-oz_46_165.png\" width=\"46\" height=\"165\" /></a>Goose Island Sofie</h3>\r\n<h5>BELGIAN ALE</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 6.5%</h5>\r\nFermented with wild yeasts and aged in wine barrels with orange peel, Sofie is a tart, dry, sparkling ale. A subtle, spicy white pepper note, a hint of citrus from the orange peel and a creamy vanilla finish make Sofie an intriguing choice for Champagne drinkers and beer drinkers who are fond of Belgian Saisons.\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Goose_Island_Matilda_12-oz._46_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2429\" alt=\"Goose_Island_Matilda_12-oz._46_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Goose_Island_Matilda_12-oz._46_165.png\" width=\"46\" height=\"165\" /></a>Goose Island Matilde</h3>\r\n<h5>PALE ALE</h5>\r\n<h5>YEAR ROUND</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 7%</h5>\r\nWild in character, with a slightly fruity aroma and a spicy yeast flavor that is as unique as it is satisfying - Matilda is an intriguing choice for beer and wine lovers alike. Dry and quenching, it\'s the perfect accompaniment at the dining table or for casually socializing at the bar.\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Goose_Island_Winter_Mild_btl_70x273_clr_42_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2431\" alt=\"Goose_Island_Winter_Mild_btl_70x273_clr_42_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Goose_Island_Winter_Mild_btl_70x273_clr_42_165.png\" width=\"42\" height=\"165\" /></a>Goose Island Mild Winter</h3>\r\n<h5>MILD ALE</h5>\r\n<h5>YEAR ROUND</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 5.6%</h5>\r\nToffee brown, medium-bodied, with a creamy head and an aroma of raisins and freshly baked dark bread. Mild Winter\'s rich caramel malt and spicy rye flavors are sure to take the bite out of whatever Old Man Winter brews up for you this year.\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Goose_Island_Pere_Jacques_12-oz._46_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2428\" alt=\"Goose_Island_Pere_Jacques_12-oz._46_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Goose_Island_Pere_Jacques_12-oz._46_165.png\" width=\"46\" height=\"165\" /></a>Goose Island Pere Jacques</h3>\r\n<h5>BELGIAN ALE</h5>\r\n<h5>YEAR ROUND</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 8.7%</h5>\r\nBrewed with loads of malt and Belgian yeast, Pere Jacques is a wonderfully fruity, malty ale. Pere Jacques\' complex flavors stand shoulder to shoulder with the Belgian Dubbels enjoyed in the world\'s finest beer bars. At the dining table it\'s the perfect alternative to a glass of vintage port.\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Goose_Island_Pepe_Nero_12-oz_46_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2427\" alt=\"Goose_Island_Pepe_Nero_12-oz_46_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Goose_Island_Pepe_Nero_12-oz_46_165.png\" width=\"46\" height=\"165\" /></a>Goose Island Pepe Nero</h3>\r\n<h5>BELGIAN ALE</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 6.4%</h5>\r\nWith an aroma of roasted chestnuts and a mysteriously dark, mahogany hue, Pepe Nero is a farmhouse ale brewed with black peppercorns. His roasty sweetness melds into a lingering, earthy, black pepper finish that is ideal for pairing with grilled meats and roasted vegetables.'),
