	(7132,2169,'_mcb-products','[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n\r\n<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]</span>\r\n<h3><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: 15px; font-weight: bold;\"><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Stella-Bottle-cold-2013_45_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2497\" alt=\"Stella-Bottle-cold-2013_45_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Stella-Bottle-cold-2013_45_165.png\" width=\"45\" height=\"165\" /></a></span></h3>\r\n<h4>Stella Artois</h4>\r\n<h5>LAGER</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 5.2%</h5>\r\n1926 saw the birth of one of the most important additions to the family, Stella Artois. Stella, the Latin word for star, was first introduced in celebration of the festive season. It was an instant sensation, and became so popular that it stayed in demand throughout history, and for decades to come. Today, Stella Artois is renowned as a quality beer conditioned for an average of 6 – 11 days longer than most other beers.\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Stella-Artois-Cidre-2013_46_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2496\" alt=\"Stella-Artois-Cidre-2013_46_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Stella-Artois-Cidre-2013_46_165.png\" width=\"46\" height=\"165\" /></a></h3>\r\n<h4>Stella Cidre</h4>\r\n<h5>BELGIAN CIDER</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 5%</h5>\r\nCrisp and refreshing Belgian cider made with hand-picked apples (50%).\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h3 style=\"font-size: 1.17em;\"><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Hoegaarden_witbier_90x_46_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2495\" alt=\"Hoegaarden_witbier_90x_46_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Hoegaarden_witbier_90x_46_165.png\" width=\"46\" height=\"165\" /></a></h3>\r\n<h4>Hoegaarden</h4>\r\n<h5>WITBIER</h5>\r\n<h5>YEAR ROUND</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 4.9%</h5>\r\nThe original wheat beer is the oldest and most famous of Hoegaarden\'s range. When poured, it forms a soft, white creamy head and leaves a generous lacing on the glass. It is naturally cloudy, pale hue shimmers when viewed through the glass.\r\n\r\nWith an aroma of orange peel, coriander and spice, its characteristic taste is entirely unique: smooth, light-bodied, and simultaneously sweet and sour, with a subtle, spiced citrus flavour. Best served in its traditional hexagonal glass.\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h4><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Spaten_Premium_Lager_70x249_46_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2494\" alt=\"Spaten_Premium_Lager_70x249_46_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Spaten_Premium_Lager_70x249_46_165.png\" width=\"46\" height=\"165\" /></a>Spaten Premium Lager</h4>\r\n<h5>CLASSIC GERMAN PREMIUM LAGER</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 5.2%</h5>\r\nPremium brand, bottom fermented Munchner Lager with a supremely well balanced hop flavor.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 style=\"font-size: 1.17em;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: 13px; font-weight: normal;\">[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]</span></h3>\r\n<h4><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Spaten_Oktoberfest_btl_70x269_clr_43_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2493\" alt=\"Spaten_Oktoberfest_btl_70x269_clr_43_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Spaten_Oktoberfest_btl_70x269_clr_43_165.png\" width=\"43\" height=\"165\" /></a>Spaten Octoberfest</h4>\r\n<h5>WORLD\'S FIRST OKTOBERFEST BEER</h5>\r\n<h5>YEAR ROUND</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 5.9%</h5>\r\nThe beer of Munich\'s famous Oktoberfest: aromatic, savoury, gold-colored.\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h4>Franziskaner Hefeweisse</h4>\r\n<h5><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Franziskaner_btl_70x266_clr_43_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2491\" alt=\"Franziskaner_btl_70x266_clr_43_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Franziskaner_btl_70x266_clr_43_165.png\" width=\"43\" height=\"165\" /></a>HEFEWEIZEN</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 5%</h5>\r\nFranziskaner Hefe-Weisse is noted for its agreeable level of carbonation and its natural cloudiness. It is brewed from wheat malt, barley malt, hops, top-fermenting yeast and water according to a time-honoured Bavarian recipe. Brewed in strict adherence to the Bavarian Purity Law of 1516.\r\n<div></div>\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h4><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Franziskaner_Hefe_Dunkel_69x253_clr_45_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2492\" alt=\"Franziskaner_Hefe_Dunkel_69x253_clr_45_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Franziskaner_Hefe_Dunkel_69x253_clr_45_165.png\" width=\"45\" height=\"165\" /></a>Franziskaner  Hefeweisse Dunkel</h4>\r\n<h5>DUNKELWEIZEN</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 5%</h5>\r\nHefe-Weisse Dunkel is top-fermented, noted for agreeable carbonation levels and zesty wheat flavor. The consistently high quality makes Franziskaner weiss beers a refreshing taste sensation . Brewed in strict adherence to the Bavarian Purity Law of 1516.\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h4><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/leffe-blonde.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2490\" alt=\"leffe blonde\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/leffe-blonde.jpg\" width=\"46\" height=\"163\" /></a>Leffe Blonde</h4>\r\n<h5>BELGIAN ABBEY ALE</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 6.6%</h5>\r\nLeffe Blonde is a dry, fruity, lightly spiced Belgian Abbey Ale, quite full and creamy; a perfect balance of strength and subtlety.\r\n\r\nThe bitterness is delicate, extending over the whole palette and lingering as a subtle aftertaste. Leffe should be served slightly warmer than usual at 41°F to allow its distinct aromatic characteristics to escape and should always be served in its proprietary Chalice glass. Leffe is brewed to the same recipe as it was in 1240.\r\n\r\n[xt_divider style=\"shadow\"]\r\n<h4><a href=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/bass-pale-ale_45_165.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-2489\" alt=\"bass-pale-ale_45_165\" src=\"http://cfhq.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/bass-pale-ale_45_165.png\" width=\"45\" height=\"165\" /></a>Bass Pale Ale</h4>\r\n<h5>PALE ALE</h5>\r\n<h5>ABV: 5%</h5>\r\nThe precise combination of Bass Pale Ale and stout resulted in a flavor like no other. Its popularity quickly spread throughout Britain and Ireland, ultimately reaching the United States.\r\n\r\nSo toast history as you pour yourself a Black &amp; Tan, Bass’ distinctive caramel notes with hints of nuts and plum to make it an authentic Black &amp; Tan.'),
